<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN POST CHAIRMAN TO QUIT JOB MARCH 3
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 2 (CNA) 03/02/07  21:48:41 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
Taiwan Post Co. Chairman Lai Ching-chi will leave his job
Saturday, with Vice Minister of Transportation and Communications
Ho Nuan-hsuan designated to serve as acting chairman of the
state-owned company.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Transportation and Communications Tsai Duei said that
since Lai was firm in his decision to resign, he could not but
approve his resignation, formally presented Feb. 28. He added
that Lai expressed his intention to quit his post prior to the
Chinese New Year holiday.
</P>
<P>
Lai, who took up the chairmanship nine months ago, said he
decided to resign his post after achieving the mission of
changing the company's name from "Chunghwa Post Co." to "Taiwan
Post Co." under a name-rectification campaign launched by the
government.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan Post board of directors will hold a meeting Saturday
to approve Ho's designation as the company's acting chairman.
</P>
